2026-04-13 15:25:08,951 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: We have loaded the input workbook and inspected the first sheet. It contains 16 rows and 6 columns. Column B (index 2) holds the original word, and column C (index 3) holds the converted word (simple present tense). The task is to ensure that the first letter of the converted word matches the case (upper/lower) of the first letter of the original word. We'll iterate over all data rows, adjust the first character of the value in column C accordingly, write the corrected value back, and then save the workbook to the output folder preserving the original filename. Finally we will verify a few rows to confirm the changes.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl, os

# Paths
input_path = "/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_47842_init.xlsx"
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, "1_47842_init.xlsx")

# Load workbook (read/write)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # assume first sheet contains the data

# Process rows (skip header row 1)
for row in range(2, ws.max_row + 1):
    orig_cell = ws.cell(row=row, column=2)   # Column B
    conv_cell = ws.cell(row=row, column=3)   # Column C

    orig = orig_cell.value
    conv = conv_cell.value

    # Only process if both are strings
    if isinstance(orig, str) and isinstance(conv, str) and conv:
        # Preserve the rest of the word, adjust only the first character case
        first_orig = orig[0]
        rest_conv = conv[1:] if len(conv) > 1 else ""
        if first_orig.isupper():
            new_conv = first_orig.upper() + rest_conv
        else:
            new_conv = first_orig.lower() + rest_conv
        # Write back if changed
        if new_conv != conv:
            conv_cell.value = new_conv

# Ensure output directory exists
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Save the modified workbook
wb.save(output_path)

# Verify a few rows after modification
print("Verification of first 5 data rows after correction:")
for row in range(2, min(7, ws.max_row + 1)):
    orig = ws.cell(row=row, column=2).value
    conv = ws.cell(row=row, column=3).value
    print(f"Row {row}: Original='{orig}' | Converted='{conv}'")
```
